"title": "8310: morality, and creation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8310",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Human beings have been created moral creatures in the likeness of God, who is the source and standard of all that is good.</p>\n<h2>Morality is grounded in the nature of God himself</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:4\">DEU 32:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:18-Luke18:19\">LUK 18:18–18:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:19\">EXO 33:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:5-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:5–34:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps25:8-Ps25:9\">PSA 25:8–25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:68\">PSA 119:68</a></p>\n<h2>Human beings are morally aware</h2>\n<h3>They are created in God's image</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26-Gen1:27\">GEN 1:26–1:27</a></p>\n<h3>They have a conscience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:14-Rom2:15\">ROM 2:14–2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:2\">2CO 4:2</a></p>\n<h3>They have been given a moral law</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:16-Gen2:17\">GEN 2:16–2:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:6-Mark10:9\">MRK 10:6–10:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen2:23-Gen2:24\">GEN 2:23–2:24</a> <em>Standards for marriage are implicit in the creation.</em></p>\n<h3>They are capable of sharing moral ideals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:9\">JHN 1:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:1–13:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:15\">EPH 3:15</a> <em>“whole family” is literally “all fatherhood”, implying that every understanding of fatherhood and family is derived from God</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:8\">PHP 4:8</a> <em>refering to pagan virtues</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">TIT 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Immoral acts are unnatural</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a></p>\n<h3>God's judgment implies moral responsibility</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:10\">JER 17:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:20-Ezek18:21\">EZK 18:20–18:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:6\">AMO 1:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5-Rom2:11\">ROM 2:5–2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Human beings are morally flawed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23\">ROM 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps64:6\">PSA 64:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa32:6\">ISA 32:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9\">JER 17:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:28-Rom1:32\">ROM 1:28–1:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:7\">ROM 8:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:2\">1TI 4:2</a></p>",
